I honestly think this is extremely underrated right now, and [Gideon Jura](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Gideon Jura) is overrated simply because control players are starved to hell. I'm not going to go into magical christmasland with dream scenarios about 20 dragons in play and you use [Sarkhan the Mad](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sarkhan the Mad)'s final, but he's very useful for taking out Eldrazi and certain 5/5 flying lifelinking first striking angels. At this week's FNM, my opponent was on the play and on his turn 5 he sacced all his spawn tokens and made a [Spawnsire of Ulamog](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Spawnsire of Ulamog).. On my turn I dropped [Sarkhan the Mad](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sarkhan the Mad) and converted it into a 5/5 dragon. Needless to say, he was \*\*\*ed. Very useful utility card, and I expect him to see a lot of play.  


